Metal plates? Peg leg?

246
00:10:44.043 --> 00:10:45.254
Wait. Wait.
What are you doing?

247
00:10:45.278 --> 00:10:47.023
- What are you doing?
- Calling your bluff.

248
00:10:50.033 --> 00:10:53.379
Seven-Adam-19.
we need an RA to 117 Ayers.

249
00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:55.523
Thirty-year-old male.
severe trauma to left leg.

250
00:10:58.458 --> 00:11:00.252
You're lucky
his leg's gonna be okay.

251
00:11:00.276 --> 00:11:01.537
If Murphy hadn't gotten
in my head.

252
00:11:01.561 --> 00:11:04.081
that never would've happened.
Blame the reversals. not me.

253
00:11:04.481 --> 00:11:05.824
What happened between you two?

254
00:11:05.848 --> 00:11:07.443
Did she investigate you
or something?

255
00:11:07.467 --> 00:11:08.587
Indirectly.

256
00:11:11.688 --> 00:11:12.903
Is it Isabel?

257
00:11:15.642 --> 00:11:17.503
Look. Murphy
was her investigating officer.

258
00:11:17.527 --> 00:11:20.339
Okay. but you're not Isabel.
so what's her beef with you?

259
00:11:20.363 --> 00:11:22.803
Not your concern.
Start the paperwork.

260
00:11:25.134 --> 00:11:26.646
- Everything okay?
- Yes. ma'am.

261
00:11:26.670 --> 00:11:29.348
Uh. we had a reversal.
But Officer Bradford

262
00:11:29.372 --> 00:11:31.092
- saw right through it. so...
- I heard.

263
00:11:31.290 --> 00:11:33.018
IA is stepping up their game
using celebrities.

264
00:11:33.042 --> 00:11:34.386
- Yeah.
- Stay vigilant.

265
00:11:34.410 --> 00:11:36.322
Hmm.
I wanted to say.

266
00:11:36.346 --> 00:11:38.824
I really appreciated
what you said earlier today.

267
00:11:38.848 --> 00:11:41.544
about cops doing
the right thing every day.

268
00:11:41.568 --> 00:11:44.146
Is that because
you're seeing evidence
of officers acting otherwise?

269
00:11:44.170 --> 00:11:45.170
No.

270
00:11:45.338 --> 00:11:47.583
- Not at all. I... I was just...
- Relax. Officer Chen.

271
00:11:47.607 --> 00:11:49.952
I'm not gonna ask you
to narc on anyone.

272
00:11:49.976 --> 00:11:51.703
But part of protecting
and serving...

273
00:11:51.727 --> 00:11:54.207
is making sure you refuse to do
anything that crosses a line.

274
00:11:54.464 --> 00:11:56.158
So. if anybody is asking you
to do so.

275
00:11:56.182 --> 00:11:57.343
I expect you to come talk to me.

276
00:11:57.367 --> 00:11:59.078
- Yes. ma'am.
- Okay.

277
00:11:59.102 --> 00:12:00.796
Tell me.
how's that new apartment
working out?

278
00:12:00.820 --> 00:12:03.849
Oh! Uh. it's great.
It's in a quiet neighborhood.

279
00:12:03.873 --> 00:12:06.458
There's lots of coffee shops
and people walking around.

280
00:12:09.762 --> 00:12:10.762
Ah.

281
00:12:11.430 --> 00:12:12.430
Comics?

282
00:12:13.350 --> 00:12:16.234
Yeah. uh. I found it
in the lost and found.

283
00:12:17.036 --> 00:12:19.396
And by lost and found.
I mean my locker.

284
00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:21.622
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

285
00:12:24.093 --> 00:12:27.756
- So. what happens now?
- I... Your sister. she's...

286
00:12:27.780 --> 00:12:29.058
she's stable.

287
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:31.348
And no reason why she can't make
a full recovery.

288
00:12:31.767 --> 00:12:32.900
Then it's up to her.

289
00:12:33.770 --> 00:12:35.119
But ODs have a way of uh...

290
00:12:35.805 --> 00:12:37.085
putting things into perspective.

291
00:12:38.191 --> 00:12:40.325
My mom OD'd three times
before she died.

292
00:12:41.378 --> 00:12:43.344
Each time she swore
she was gonna get clean.

293
00:12:45.198 --> 00:12:47.565
Cassie and I found her
when we went down for breakfast.

294
00:12:48.317 --> 00:12:50.435
- She was blue.
- Yeah.

295
00:12:51.271 --> 00:12:52.751
- You can't lose hope.
- Yeah.

296
00:12:53.173 --> 00:12:55.440
- That's what everyone says.
- 'Cause it's true. Jake.

297
00:12:57.511 --> 00:12:59.972
Social Services is on their way
to get you placed somewhere safe

298
00:12:59.996 --> 00:13:01.636
while your sister gets the help
she needs.

299
00:13:02.182 --> 00:13:03.931
- Okay?
- Sure.

300
00:13:08.188 --> 00:13:09.220
I'll be right back.

301
00:13:10.456 --> 00:13:12.623
Hey. Hold up. Can we talk?

302
00:13:13.726 --> 00:13:14.759
Okay.

303
00:13:18.848 --> 00:13:20.198
I need to explain something.

304
00:13:21.801 --> 00:13:23.201
My dad left when I was a kid.

305
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:25.536
and my mom never really got
past it.

306
00:13:25.888 --> 00:13:29.040
There was no one stable growing
up in my life. so...

307
00:13:29.526 --> 00:13:31.904
I guess what I'm trying to say
is I think that's the reason

308
00:13:31.928 --> 00:13:34.161
why I... I...
I went through your phone.

309
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.878
- You sound like my clients.
- What?

310
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:41.119
Everybody's dad bailed.
No one's mom was perfect.

311
00:13:43.122 --> 00:13:45.901
- Doesn't change what you did.
- No. I know. but...

312
00:13:45.925 --> 00:13:47.069
You're a grown woman.

313
00:13:47.093 --> 00:13:49.810
So having a bad childhood.
isn't a valid excuse anymore.

314
00:13:50.763 --> 00:13:53.765
Look. I wish I could trust you
again. but...

315
00:13:55.168 --> 00:13:56.183
I don't see how I can.

316
00:13:58.688 --> 00:13:59.704
I'm sorry.

317
00:14:07.647 --> 00:14:09.826
Tim was so convinced
we caught another reversal.

318
00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:12.111
he pried open the bear trap.

319
00:14:12.135 --> 00:14:14.397
I've never seen someone actually
pass out from pain before.

320
00:14:14.421 --> 00:14:15.421
That's tough.

321
00:14:15.638 --> 00:14:18.078
But not as bad
as the helplessness
in that kid's eyes.

322
00:14:19.659 --> 00:14:21.571
What about you?
Good day? Bad day?

323
00:14:21.595 --> 00:14:25.029
I had to pry a psycho off
a valet at a five-star hotel.

324
00:14:25.414 --> 00:14:28.477
Uh. her dress ripped
as I was cuffing her.

325
00:14:28.501 --> 00:14:30.421
exposing her unmentionables.
Boy. she was pissed.

326
00:14:30.820 --> 00:14:32.300
- Wow.
- What?

327
00:14:32.873 --> 00:14:34.800
That was for sure a reversal.

328
00:14:34.824 --> 00:14:37.569
Yeah. dress was probably rigged.
like break-away pants.

329
00:14:37.593 --> 00:14:38.888
- Mm-hmm.
- That's what I thought!

330
00:14:38.912 --> 00:14:40.640
- Yeah?
- Oh.

331
00:14:40.664 --> 00:14:43.342
Okay. I see what you're doing.
Can I get that to go. please?

332
00:14:43.366 --> 00:14:44.777
No. come on! Don't be like that!

333
00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:45.978
No. as much as I would love

334
00:14:46.002 --> 00:14:48.130
to keep telling war stories...
Thank you. Dez.

335
00:14:48.154 --> 00:14:50.348
I have another full day
of reversals tomorrow.

336
00:14:50.372 --> 00:14:52.067
and this rookie
needs his beauty sleep.

337
00:15:43.425 --> 00:15:44.525
Hey.

338
00:15:44.877 --> 00:15:46.856
So. they canvassed the area.
No one saw the shooter.

339
00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:48.224
He fired
a couple hundred rounds.

340
00:15:48.248 --> 00:15:49.859
Yeah. no one's admitting
they saw him.

341
00:15:49.883 --> 00:15:51.610
Yeah. patrol found the car
he escaped in.

342
00:15:51.634 --> 00:15:53.145
It was reported stolen
this afternoon.

343
00:15:53.169 --> 00:15:55.280
- SID is all over it.
- Who'd you piss off?

344
00:15:55.304 --> 00:15:57.082
Clearly someone with access
to heavy weaponry.

345
00:15:57.106 --> 00:15:58.386
I didn't recognize the guy.

346
00:15:58.558 --> 00:16:01.036
According to intelligence.
you've been green-lit
by Southern Front.

347
00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:03.055
- Green-lit?
- Means they put a hit on you.

348
00:16:03.079 --> 00:16:04.811
How's a rookie get green-lit
before me?

349
00:16:05.197 --> 00:16:07.125
- I gotta step up my game.
- It's not a badge of honor.

350
00:16:07.149 --> 00:16:08.961
Violent white supremacist gang
wants you dead.

351
00:16:08.985 --> 00:16:10.512
- you're doing something right.
- I... I'm sorry.

352
00:16:10.536 --> 00:16:13.782
White supremacy gang
and green-lit. w... what?
What the hell is going on?

353
00:16:13.806 --> 00:16:16.406
Normally.
gangs don't target cops.
more trouble than it's worth.

354
00:16:16.509 --> 00:16:19.037
Unless a cop disrespects
a gang member.

355
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:21.256
- then all bets are off.
- You arrested a woman today.

356
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:22.346
Astrid Heisserer.

357
00:16:23.883 --> 00:16:26.045
Her dress broke.
I... I embarrassed her.

358
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:27.218
I thought she was IA.

359
00:16:27.654 --> 00:16:30.315
She's not.
She's the baby mama
of the leader of Southern Front.

360
00:16:30.339 --> 00:16:33.051
one of the most violent
criminal enterprises
in the country.

361
00:16:33.075 --> 00:16:34.603
And because
of how you treated her.

362
00:16:34.627 --> 00:16:36.922
he authorized everyone
in the gang to kill you.

363
00:16:36.946 --> 00:16:39.124
- What about Talia?
- Yeah. what about me?

364
00:16:39.148 --> 00:16:40.792
Nolan is the one
who put hands on her.

365
00:16:40.816 --> 00:16:43.696
- He's the one they're after.
- How many Southern Front members
are there?

366
00:16:43.769 --> 00:16:45.319
In the greater Los Angeles area?

367
00:16:45.821 --> 00:16:48.941
- Several thousand.
- And protecting you will be
our number-one priority.

368
00:16:48.991 --> 00:16:50.786
Step one is to get you
off the streets.

369
00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:53.130
Come with me. Nolan.
I'm gonna escort you home.

370
00:17:00.420 --> 00:17:02.660
K9 unit already swept
the property.

371
00:17:03.306 --> 00:17:05.234
- Owner coming home tonight?
- Uh. no.

372
00:17:05.258 --> 00:17:08.703
Ben left for New York yesterday.
So. what's happening here?

373
00:17:08.727 --> 00:17:10.728
The DA approved a VARDA alarm.

374
00:17:11.231 --> 00:17:13.159
It bypasses 911.
sends a red alert

375
00:17:13.183 --> 00:17:14.463
to all the cops in the area.

376
00:17:14.934 --> 00:17:16.379
So. what's next?

377
00:17:16.403 --> 00:17:17.546
That's up to you.

378
00:17:17.570 --> 00:17:19.197
I mean.
I can't just go to work. right?

379
00:17:19.221 --> 00:17:21.666
I'd be endangering everyone
who came within five feet of me.

380
00:17:21.690 --> 00:17:23.185
Being a cop is being at risk.

381
00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:25.049
So you're saying
I should just...

382
00:17:25.094 --> 00:17:27.014
report for duty.
act like nothing happened?

383
00:17:27.163 --> 00:17:29.575
I think we tell criminals
what to do.
not the other way around.

384
00:17:29.599 --> 00:17:31.999
- No matter the consequences?
- No matter the consequences.

385
00:17:32.451 --> 00:17:34.446
But. look. it's up to you.

386
00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:36.165
No one is gonna judge you.
either way.

387
00:17:36.189 --> 00:17:37.709
- Yeah. right.
- Nolan.

388
00:17:39.292 --> 00:17:41.859
This isn't about bravery.
You have a family.

389
00:17:42.645 --> 00:17:44.845
Any cop who's ever worn a badge
understands that.

390
00:17:45.698 --> 00:17:47.276
All set. Captain.

391
00:17:47.300 --> 00:17:48.510
Okay.

392
00:17:48.534 --> 00:17:50.395
It seems the system is up
and armed.

393
00:17:50.419 --> 00:17:52.579
We have a unit parked out front.
Try to get some sleep.

394
00:17:53.355 --> 00:17:55.939
- Don't see that happening.
- No.

395
00:17:56.659 --> 00:17:58.339
- Thank you.
- Have a good night.

396
00:17:59.812 --> 00:18:02.997
- Hey. What are you doing here?
- Guard duty.

397
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:06.100
- I think we have that covered.
- Now. it's extra covered.

398
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:09.448
You call me directly.
if anything happens.

399
00:18:09.472 --> 00:18:10.716
- Yes. ma'am.
- Mm-hmm.

400
00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:11.860
Okay.

401
00:18:14.727 --> 00:18:16.767
West and Chen.
reporting for duty.

402
00:18:17.297 --> 00:18:21.359
Guys. this is very sweet.
But honestly. it's unnecessary.

403
00:18:21.383 --> 00:18:22.733
You'd do the same for us.

404
00:18:23.852 --> 00:18:25.497
So. how do you want to do this?

405
00:18:25.521 --> 00:18:27.616
Personally. I'd go
with alternating two-hour shifts

406
00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:29.607
with a static position.
plus a rover.

407
00:18:30.109 --> 00:18:32.776
Oh. and I have earpieces.
and walkies.

408
00:18:33.228 --> 00:18:35.108
just so we can keep
in constant contact.

409
00:18:35.598 --> 00:18:36.775
- You got anything sweet?
- Yeah.

410
00:18:36.799 --> 00:18:38.319
- I think there's some ice cream.
- Mm.

411
00:18:38.968 --> 00:18:40.351
Wait. guys. Guys!

412
00:18:40.770 --> 00:18:42.610
Look. come on.
We need to stay focused.

413
00:18:43.806 --> 00:18:45.551
You know. the whole point
of guard duty

414
00:18:45.575 --> 00:18:46.952
is that we take turns being up.

415
00:18:46.976 --> 00:18:49.371
- so everyone gets some sleep.
- You could've left any time.

416
00:18:49.395 --> 00:18:51.389
Yup.
No one would've given you grief.

417
00:18:51.413 --> 00:18:53.408
- Yeah. right.
- Oh.

418
00:18:53.432 --> 00:18:55.566
We got to get to the station.
Our shift starts soon.

419
00:18:56.319 --> 00:18:58.347
- I should go in.
- What. to work?

420
00:18:58.371 --> 00:19:01.055
Absolutely not.
You're safest right here.

421
00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:03.301
We'll manage without you
for a few weeks at work.

422
00:19:03.325 --> 00:19:04.470
What if it's longer than that?

423
00:19:04.494 --> 00:19:06.534
My training would be
put on hold. I'd...

424
00:19:07.262 --> 00:19:09.196
stay a rookie
while you guys moved up.

425
00:19:09.882 --> 00:19:10.882
We'd be separated.

426
00:19:13.036 --> 00:19:14.418
That's never gonna happen.

427
00:19:15.588 --> 00:19:17.588
This. uh...
This'll all be over soon.

428
00:19:17.640 --> 00:19:19.120
- Yeah.
- And if it's not?

429
00:19:20.276 --> 00:19:23.210
Then it's good you have a pool.

430
00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:33.082
Sorry. everyone. settle down.

431
00:19:33.106 --> 00:19:34.867
- Captain.
- Thank you for coming in.

432
00:19:34.891 --> 00:19:37.152
Most of you on your day off.
Till this is resolved.

433
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.096
all overtime limits
have been lifted.

434
00:19:40.246 --> 00:19:41.412
As you may know.

435
00:19:42.115 --> 00:19:45.277
Southern Front originated
as a white supremacist
prison gang.

436
00:19:45.301 --> 00:19:47.295
about 15 years ago.
Since then.

437
00:19:47.319 --> 00:19:48.780
they have branched out
in a big way.

438
00:19:48.804 --> 00:19:50.771
Drugs. prostitution. extortion.

439
00:19:51.324 --> 00:19:52.701
But what sets them apart.

440
00:19:52.725 --> 00:19:54.605
is their access
to military weapons.

441
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:57.177
Their leader.
the so-called King Midas.

442
00:19:57.529 --> 00:20:00.748
is currently serving three
consecutive life sentences.

443
00:20:01.133 --> 00:20:04.318
His son. Cole. he controls
the day-to-day operations
on the street.

444
00:20:04.754 --> 00:20:07.666
But make no mistake. his father
is pulling the strings.

445
00:20:07.690 --> 00:20:10.257
Lifting the green light would be
a huge loss of face for Cole.

446
00:20:10.876 --> 00:20:12.137
So he's not
gonna do it willingly.

447
00:20:12.161 --> 00:20:13.856
So we gotta make
this a business decision.

448
00:20:13.880 --> 00:20:15.924
We put a big enough hurt
on their operation.

449
00:20:15.948 --> 00:20:17.314
they'll lift the green light.

450
00:20:21.453 --> 00:20:22.453
Sorry. I'm late.

451
00:20:49.615 --> 00:20:52.366
Yesterday. Southern Front
tried to kill one of our own.

452
00:20:53.786 --> 00:20:55.702
Today. we hit back.

453
00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:05.710
- What?
- Nothing.

454
00:21:06.299 --> 00:21:08.677
Look. everyone else
sees this big hero move.

455
00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:11.421
but I see your ego
getting in the way
of you doing the smart thing.

456
00:21:12.221 --> 00:21:13.236
Look.

457
00:21:14.106 --> 00:21:15.350
If you don't wanna ride
with me...

458
00:21:15.374 --> 00:21:17.285
It's not about my safety.

459
00:21:17.309 --> 00:21:18.687
It's about yours.

460
00:21:18.711 --> 00:21:20.739
You're risking your life
to prove a point.

461
00:21:20.763 --> 00:21:22.057
Seems worth it to me.

462
00:21:22.081 --> 00:21:23.361
if you're making
the right point.

463
00:21:23.966 --> 00:21:25.806
But there's no sense
in taking a needless risk.

464
00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:27.896
Which is why Officer Nolan
will be staying far away

465
00:21:27.920 --> 00:21:29.420
from anything
Southern Front related.

466
00:21:30.406 --> 00:21:31.526
And I'll be riding with him.

467
00:21:33.075 --> 00:21:34.903
Whether I agree
with his decision or not.

468
00:21:34.927 --> 00:21:36.155
he's my rookie.

469
00:21:36.179 --> 00:21:37.419
And I'll take good care of him.

470
00:21:39.648 --> 00:21:40.848
Yes. ma'am.

471
00:21:44.486 --> 00:21:45.697
Riding with the captain.

472
00:21:45.721 --> 00:21:47.481
And I thought. being green-lit
was scary.

473
00:21:47.973 --> 00:21:49.573
- I drive.
- Of course.

474
00:21:50.459 --> 00:21:51.508
Officer Nolan.

475
00:21:52.178 --> 00:21:53.658
- Keys.
- Yes.

476
00:21:55.498 --> 00:21:58.210
How exactly
are we hurting Midas' operation?

477
00:21:58.234 --> 00:22:00.594
By attacking Southern Front
where they make all their money.

478
00:22:00.703 --> 00:22:02.343
the three Ts.

479
00:22:03.272 --> 00:22:04.616
<i>Drug trafficking...</i>

480
00:22:07.893 --> 00:22:09.042
<i>Weapons trafficking...</i>

481
00:22:11.880 --> 00:22:12.920
<i>And sex trafficking.</i>

482
00:22:26.728 --> 00:22:27.972
I'll handle processing.

483
00:22:27.996 --> 00:22:29.676
You get started
on the asset paperwork.

484
00:22:29.899 --> 00:22:32.311
I still don't see how
confiscating 20 gallons of lube

485
00:22:32.335 --> 00:22:33.811
is gonna get the gang
to back off Nolan.

486
00:22:33.835 --> 00:22:36.116
Asset forfeiture is where
we do the most damage today.

487
00:22:36.288 --> 00:22:38.250
Law says we can seize everything
and anything connected

488
00:22:38.274 --> 00:22:39.354
to their illegal operation.

489
00:22:39.726 --> 00:22:42.270
Vehicles. merchandise.
even the massage parlor.

490
00:22:42.294 --> 00:22:44.406
Well. so.
why didn't we hit it last week?

491
00:22:44.430 --> 00:22:46.291
Vice knew that Southern Front
owned that shop.

492
00:22:46.315 --> 00:22:48.142
'Cause it's whack-a-mole.
You take out
one criminal enterprise.

493
00:22:48.166 --> 00:22:49.444
another one takes its place.

494
00:22:49.468 --> 00:22:51.029
Usually. not a good use
of our time.

495
00:22:51.053 --> 00:22:52.364
But today.
that's exactly what we want.

496
00:22:52.388 --> 00:22:54.332
Make sure Southern Front's
scared one of their competitors

497
00:22:54.356 --> 00:22:56.516
- is about to move in...
- Don't touch me.

498
00:22:56.725 --> 00:22:57.958
You gotta be kidding me.

499
00:22:59.996 --> 00:23:01.339
What the hell
are you doing here?

500
00:23:01.363 --> 00:23:03.141
My job. making sure cops
don't break the law.

501
00:23:03.165 --> 00:23:04.626
One of our officers
was green-lit.

502
00:23:04.650 --> 00:23:05.960
Came within seconds
of being killed.

503
00:23:05.984 --> 00:23:08.230
When do you think that a cop's
most likely to cross the line?

504
00:23:08.254 --> 00:23:10.048
When they're scared. angry.
and want revenge.

505
00:23:10.072 --> 00:23:12.432
They might. I don't know.
yell at a detective.

506
00:23:12.708 --> 00:23:15.254
How about I write you up
for conduct unbecoming
an officer?

507
00:23:15.278 --> 00:23:16.487
Knock yourself out.

508
00:23:16.511 --> 00:23:18.106
This is about Isabel
and you know it.

509
00:23:18.130 --> 00:23:19.441
You know it is about Isabel.

510
00:23:19.465 --> 00:23:21.759
It's about the fact
that you covered for her
for months.

511
00:23:21.783 --> 00:23:23.444
- That's not true.
- Oh. please.

512
00:23:23.468 --> 00:23:25.580
Any cop can tell an addict
ten miles out.

513
00:23:25.604 --> 00:23:27.415
You knew she was using.
and you let her come to work

514
00:23:27.439 --> 00:23:28.717
every day with a loaded gun.

515
00:23:28.741 --> 00:23:30.752
You had an obligation
to report her and you didn't.

516
00:23:30.776 --> 00:23:32.938
Okay. that's a lie.
But I'd expect nothing less

517
00:23:32.962 --> 00:23:34.389
- from a cop like you.
- Uh. hey. I need you

518
00:23:34.413 --> 00:23:36.325
to come check something for me.
I wanna make sure I'm doing it

519
00:23:36.349 --> 00:23:37.893
by the book. okay? So. come on.

520
00:23:37.917 --> 00:23:40.712
Hey. you know what?
If I were you.
I'd ask for another T.O.

521
00:23:40.736 --> 00:23:42.986
Yeah. well.
you're not me. ma'am.

522
00:23:52.631 --> 00:23:54.910
I was told
there was a cop coming

523
00:23:54.934 --> 00:23:56.933
with the authority to negotiate.

524
00:23:57.970 --> 00:24:00.615
Cut the crap. Only color
you care about is green.

525
00:24:00.639 --> 00:24:03.657
And the LAPD has taken a lot
of that from you today.

526
00:24:04.043 --> 00:24:05.520
Now.
if you wanna stop the bleeding.

527
00:24:05.544 --> 00:24:06.727
sit your ass down.

528
00:24:12.901 --> 00:24:15.319
Look.
I reviewed the body cam footage.

529
00:24:15.754 --> 00:24:18.350
That girl tried to stab a guy
right in front of my officer.

530
00:24:18.374 --> 00:24:20.202
He used minimal force
to stop her.

531
00:24:20.226 --> 00:24:22.487
no disrespect was intended
or shown.

532
00:24:22.511 --> 00:24:24.422
Your son is overreacting.

533
00:24:24.446 --> 00:24:26.108
and I don't think
it's his first time.

534
00:24:26.132 --> 00:24:29.049
It's time for the adults
to de-escalate matters.

535
00:24:30.185 --> 00:24:32.648
- You been in the game long?
- Almost 20 years.

536
00:24:32.672 --> 00:24:35.433
Then you know
I can't just rescind
the green light.

537
00:24:35.457 --> 00:24:36.723
It's gotta come from Cole.

538
00:24:37.143 --> 00:24:40.277
Any other way.
my guys don't respect him.

539
00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:42.246
Yeah. Sucks to be you.

540
00:24:43.699 --> 00:24:46.333
Let me be clear.
I'm not here to negotiate.

541
00:24:46.686 --> 00:24:48.830
We cost you a million
in lost revenue.

542
00:24:48.854 --> 00:24:50.704
and three in seized assets.

543
00:24:51.256 --> 00:24:52.623
And we're just getting started.

544
00:24:54.043 --> 00:24:56.010
None of that matters
without honor.

545
00:24:56.379 --> 00:24:58.795
You're way out on a ledge.
Midas.

546
00:24:59.898 --> 00:25:02.961
In half a day. we shut down
seven of your businesses.

547
00:25:02.985 --> 00:25:05.196
Put 46 of your men behind bars.

548
00:25:05.220 --> 00:25:09.373
and just imagine the damage
we can do tomorrow.

549
00:25:09.825 --> 00:25:12.621
when we start hitting your spots
in San Diego.

550
00:25:12.645 --> 00:25:15.190
San Jose. Victorville.
I can keep going.

551
00:25:15.214 --> 00:25:16.214
Your son.

552
00:25:16.816 --> 00:25:19.027
is about to destroy everything
you built.

553
00:25:19.051 --> 00:25:20.811
because his girlfriend
yelled at him.

554
00:25:21.270 --> 00:25:23.770
Do the right thing.
call off the green light.

555
00:25:25.557 --> 00:25:28.403
<i>Seven-Adam-15.
possible 459 in progress.</i>

556
00:25:28.427 --> 00:25:30.121
<i>1936 Crystal Lane.</i>

557
00:25:30.145 --> 00:25:31.945
Seven-Adam-15.
show us responding.

558
00:25:32.982 --> 00:25:33.997
I hate this.

559
00:25:34.583 --> 00:25:36.812
Feels like everyone's fighting
my battle for me.

560
00:25:36.836 --> 00:25:38.168
City still needs policing.

561
00:26:15.924 --> 00:26:17.702
- Ah. that was...
- Exhilarating.

562
00:26:17.726 --> 00:26:19.109
I was gonna say terrifying.

563
00:26:21.864 --> 00:26:23.163
Guess I better get used to that.

564
00:26:23.783 --> 00:26:26.945
You know. when I. uh...
I was first stationed
in Baghdad...

565
00:26:26.969 --> 00:26:28.302
I used to get these headaches.

566
00:26:29.372 --> 00:26:31.316
Took me a few days to realize
it was 'cause my eyes

567
00:26:31.340 --> 00:26:33.420
kept darting around.
looking for trouble.

568
00:26:33.459 --> 00:26:35.420
- That's what it is.
- I didn't stop looking.

569
00:26:35.444 --> 00:26:36.676
but it does stop hurting.

570
00:26:37.963 --> 00:26:39.808
<i>Seven-Adam-15. go to channel two</i>

571
00:26:39.832 --> 00:26:41.109
<i>for Sergeant Grey.</i>

572
00:26:41.133 --> 00:26:42.133
Copy.

573
00:26:43.702 --> 00:26:45.730
- Andersen.
<i>- It worked.</i>

574
00:26:45.754 --> 00:26:47.714
<i>Midas forced Cole
to lift the green light.</i>

575
00:26:51.327 --> 00:26:53.643
I guess you are back to being
just another rookie.

576
00:26:54.196 --> 00:26:55.229
Thank God.

577
00:26:56.132 --> 00:26:58.413
- Thank you. Sergeant.
<i>- My pleasure.</i>

578
00:26:59.685 --> 00:27:02.280
So. does that mean
this little<i> Odd Couple</i>
partnership is over?

579
00:27:02.304 --> 00:27:05.005
Hell no!
We got a burglary call to take.

580
00:27:08.310 --> 00:27:11.227
Seven-Adam-15. show us Code Six
on the burglary call.

581
00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:13.191
Be advised.
we have an open door.

582
00:27:13.215 --> 00:27:14.348
Going in to clear.

583
00:27:54.823 --> 00:27:56.818
Nolan. cover!

584
00:28:01.547 --> 00:28:02.679
Hey. there!

585
00:28:23.669 --> 00:28:24.884
Look who's awake.

586
00:28:27.873 --> 00:28:29.239
Packs quite a kick. doesn't it?

587
00:28:30.526 --> 00:28:33.460
It's got four times the voltage
as LAPD uses.

588
00:28:35.281 --> 00:28:36.441
Could probably...

589
00:28:37.332 --> 00:28:39.310
cook the eyeball
right out of your skull.

590
00:28:39.334 --> 00:28:40.745
Okay. look. look.
I did not intend

591
00:28:40.769 --> 00:28:42.547
- to disrespect Astrid. okay?
- Or you. okay?

592
00:28:42.571 --> 00:28:44.165
And I would be happy
to apologize.

593
00:28:44.189 --> 00:28:45.469
Too late for that now.

594
00:28:45.857 --> 00:28:48.336
Only way this ends.
is with you dead.

595
00:28:50.312 --> 00:28:51.573
Yeah. I uh...

596
00:28:51.597 --> 00:28:53.277
I'd heard that you were dumb
but...

597
00:28:53.882 --> 00:28:55.882
it is shocking to see it
in person.

598
00:28:56.268 --> 00:28:57.788
- Dumb?
- Dumb.

599
00:28:59.538 --> 00:29:02.400
Who lured you into an ambush
with a false surrender?

600
00:29:02.424 --> 00:29:04.002
Does your father know
that it was false?

601
00:29:04.026 --> 00:29:05.058
Huh? Junior?

602
00:29:06.044 --> 00:29:08.746
I can't imagine
that revelation's
gonna go too well. huh?

603
00:29:12.501 --> 00:29:13.928
I think it'll go fine.

604
00:29:15.570 --> 00:29:19.339
Oh. he's dumber than I thought.
What's my rank?

605
00:29:20.525 --> 00:29:22.242
- What?
- What is my rank?

606
00:29:22.577 --> 00:29:25.974
Come on. you're the leader
of the sixth-largest gang
in all of California.

607
00:29:25.998 --> 00:29:28.276
Surely you can tell
from my uniform what rank I am.

608
00:29:28.300 --> 00:29:29.349
Who the hell cares?

609
00:29:30.969 --> 00:29:32.136
You're going to.

610
00:29:33.155 --> 00:29:35.050
See. it's one thing
to put a hit out on a rookie.

611
00:29:35.074 --> 00:29:36.418
- no offense.
- None taken.

612
00:29:36.442 --> 00:29:37.442
But two bars?

613
00:29:39.895 --> 00:29:42.629
Oh. for crying out loud.
And a badge that says Captain?

614
00:29:44.483 --> 00:29:46.444
You've just crossed a line
that anybody with half a brain

615
00:29:46.468 --> 00:29:48.029
would run screaming from.

616
00:29:48.053 --> 00:29:50.804
A line that even your father
might whack you for crossing.

617
00:29:51.423 --> 00:29:52.423
Understood?

618
00:29:53.408 --> 00:29:55.408
So. let me tell you
how this is gonna go.

619
00:29:55.711 --> 00:29:57.989
You and your little goonies
are gonna...

620
00:29:58.013 --> 00:29:59.680
No! Hey. Cole!

621
00:30:00.915 --> 00:30:02.310
Hurt me! Right? Don't...

622
00:30:02.334 --> 00:30:03.845
I'm the one you wanna hurt.
right?

623
00:30:03.869 --> 00:30:06.314
Killing me. that's trouble
you can handle. okay?

624
00:30:06.338 --> 00:30:07.899
But not her.
You need to let her go.

625
00:30:07.923 --> 00:30:09.363
- Do you think I'm dumb. too?
- No.

626
00:30:09.591 --> 00:30:11.031
No.

627
00:30:13.862 --> 00:30:15.982
- No!
- No!

628
00:30:17.599 --> 00:30:20.467
No! No! No!

629
00:30:23.489 --> 00:30:24.883
If the line's already
been crossed.

630
00:30:24.907 --> 00:30:26.117
then there's no going back.

631
00:30:26.141 --> 00:30:28.841
Which means neither of you
are walking out of here.

632
00:30:30.496 --> 00:30:32.040
As long as your bodies
never turn up.

633
00:30:32.064 --> 00:30:33.625
the murder can't be pinned
on me.

634
00:30:33.649 --> 00:30:36.093
- No. you're wrong.
- And Southern Front'll weather
the storm.

635
00:30:36.117 --> 00:30:39.119
It's gonna be so much worse.
You need to get her out
of there now.

636
00:30:40.088 --> 00:30:42.784
Hey. listen. What about this?
What if I...

637
00:30:42.808 --> 00:30:43.902
What if I made a video?

638
00:30:43.926 --> 00:30:46.587
I'll apologize to Astrid.
You just have to let her up.

639
00:30:46.611 --> 00:30:48.523
I already told you
that's not gonna work. man.

640
00:30:48.547 --> 00:30:50.141
- It's done.
- Think about it. Me. like this.

641
00:30:50.165 --> 00:30:51.376
And you standing over me?

642
00:30:51.400 --> 00:30:53.767
Come on. she'll eat it up.
You'll get laid for weeks.

643
00:30:56.105 --> 00:30:58.299
- Okay. yeah.
- Okay. Just get her out first.

644
00:30:58.323 --> 00:31:00.084
- Right now!
- No. you gotta make the video
first.

645
00:31:00.108 --> 00:31:01.536
- We're gonna tape... tape it.
- Come on!

646
00:31:01.560 --> 00:31:02.576
Yeah. here.

647
00:31:03.428 --> 00:31:05.856
You recording?
Hey. baby girl. this is for you!

648
00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:09.544
Astrid. I apologize.
I should not
have laid my hands on you.

649
00:31:09.568 --> 00:31:12.013
You deserved more respect
than that. I'm sorry.

650
00:31:12.037 --> 00:31:14.115
- Can we please let her up now?
- Nah. you got to do it again.

651
00:31:14.139 --> 00:31:16.117
You gotta put some feeling
into it. I didn't believe that.

652
00:31:16.141 --> 00:31:18.103
- Come on. man!
- I didn't believe you!

653
00:31:18.127 --> 00:31:19.527
- No!
- Do it again!

654
00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:25.848
Do another take. right now!
Say it with feeling!

655
00:31:47.856 --> 00:31:48.872
No!

656
00:31:57.149 --> 00:31:58.915
No! Cap!

657
00:32:16.685 --> 00:32:17.718
Come on!

658
00:32:20.855 --> 00:32:22.922
Come on. Come on. Come on.

659
00:32:24.792 --> 00:32:25.925
Come on.

660
00:32:27.012 --> 00:32:28.946
One. two. three.

661
00:32:29.348 --> 00:32:31.565
Come on! There you go. Come on.

662
00:32:31.984 --> 00:32:35.818
Come on. Come on. Come on.
Oh. come on. come on!

663
00:33:39.818 --> 00:33:40.917
It was Cole.

664
00:33:45.057 --> 00:33:47.340
Officers! Order. arms!

665
00:34:14.953 --> 00:34:16.386
Execution. arms!

666
00:34:22.160 --> 00:34:23.493
I'm so sorry.

667
00:34:59.931 --> 00:35:01.492
You're gonna give up your son.
right now!

668
00:35:01.516 --> 00:35:03.396
- The hell I am!
- He killed my captain!

669
00:35:04.819 --> 00:35:07.737
You got one chance to save him
and what's left
of your operation.

670
00:35:08.089 --> 00:35:10.329
Find out where he is.
and give him to me...

671
00:35:10.859 --> 00:35:12.392
or I'll burn your world to ash.

672
00:35:32.447 --> 00:35:33.563
Thanks.

673
00:35:36.751 --> 00:35:38.271
There'll be time
for grief later.

674
00:35:39.738 --> 00:35:40.987
We have a job to finish.

675
00:35:41.640 --> 00:35:43.656
Midas gave up his son.
We know where he's headed.

676
00:35:44.559 --> 00:35:46.576
Look.
I know what's in your hearts.

677
00:35:47.429 --> 00:35:49.290
What you want to do
more than anything.

678
00:35:49.314 --> 00:35:51.147
I'd be lying if I said
I didn't want it. too.

679
00:35:52.417 --> 00:35:54.284
Word is. you kill a cop.

680
00:35:54.670 --> 00:35:56.552
you never see the inside
of a cell.

681
00:35:59.324 --> 00:36:00.356
But that's...

682
00:36:03.044 --> 00:36:05.161
that's not what Captain Andersen
would want.

683
00:36:08.316 --> 00:36:11.278
Killing this loser
won't honor her memory.

684
00:36:11.302 --> 00:36:12.469
Doing our jobs will.

685
00:36:14.472 --> 00:36:17.073
And we owe it to her.
to do it the right way.

686
00:36:17.792 --> 00:36:19.320
- Agreed?
- Yeah.

687
00:36:22.747 --> 00:36:24.587
All right. let's go.

688
00:36:26.300 --> 00:36:28.012
All units. get ready.

689
00:36:28.036 --> 00:36:29.916
Airship has a visual.
Two minutes out.

690
00:36:30.805 --> 00:36:33.757
You were right. I was selfish.
I got her killed.

691
00:36:34.176 --> 00:36:36.876
No. Don't do that.
Don't make this about you.

692
00:36:37.396 --> 00:36:38.740
She didn't die
because of your choice.

693
00:36:38.764 --> 00:36:40.964
She died doing her job.
the only way she knew how.

694
00:36:41.466 --> 00:36:43.767
You look at it any other way.
you diminish her.

695
00:36:49.240 --> 00:36:52.036
Look. you need to know
that it doesn't matter
what happens next.

696
00:36:52.060 --> 00:36:53.787
whether we arrest this guy.
or we kill him.

697
00:36:53.811 --> 00:36:55.571
- it won't make things better.
- I know that.

698
00:36:55.964 --> 00:36:57.909
No. You only think you do.

699
00:36:57.933 --> 00:37:00.377
Please don't tell me to use it.
the grief or the anger.

700
00:37:00.401 --> 00:37:02.947
to make myself a better cop.
I can't handle that right now.

701
00:37:02.971 --> 00:37:05.238
I wasn't going to. okay?
Grief is grief. it's...

702
00:37:06.008 --> 00:37:07.351
it's a hole
that can't be filled.

703
00:37:07.375 --> 00:37:08.686
But over time.
it'll shrink enough

704
00:37:08.710 --> 00:37:10.950
so that you won't fall in
every time you take a step.

705
00:37:11.429 --> 00:37:13.091
But trust me.
if there's one thing you can use

706
00:37:13.115 --> 00:37:14.395
to make yourself a better cop.

707
00:37:14.832 --> 00:37:17.232
it'll be her life.
not her death.

708
00:37:18.637 --> 00:37:19.814
One minute!

709
00:37:19.838 --> 00:37:21.718
Think this guy'll go down
without a fight?

710
00:37:21.839 --> 00:37:23.039
I hope not.

711
00:37:28.796 --> 00:37:29.974
- Hello?
<i>- Hey.</i>

712
00:37:29.998 --> 00:37:31.798
<i>I heard what happened.
I'm so sorry.</i>

713
00:37:32.033 --> 00:37:33.661
Thanks. I...
I really can't talk right now.

714
00:37:33.685 --> 00:37:35.217
<i>I said a bunch of things
earlier.</i>

715
00:37:36.254 --> 00:37:37.870
<i>They don't really matter
right now.</i>

716
00:37:38.356 --> 00:37:39.476
<i>I wanna be here for you.</i>

717
00:37:41.542 --> 00:37:42.662
I want that. too.

718
00:37:44.012 --> 00:37:45.712
Twenty seconds out. Get ready.

719
00:37:46.181 --> 00:37:47.825
Okay.
I gotta go maybe shoot a guy.

720
00:37:47.849 --> 00:37:49.449
- Call you later.
<i>- What...</i>

721
00:38:07.485 --> 00:38:10.665
<i>Cole Midas.
you are surrounded by the LAPD.</i>

722
00:38:10.689 --> 00:38:13.423
<i>Step out of the vehicle
with your hands in the air.</i>

723
00:38:15.443 --> 00:38:19.795
- I've got a clean shot. Sarge!
<i>- Get out of the damn car. now!</i>

724
00:38:30.058 --> 00:38:31.107
Okay!

725
00:38:31.893 --> 00:38:34.094
I'm getting out! Don't shoot!

726
00:38:38.266 --> 00:38:40.750
Nolan. go arrest that man.

727
00:38:47.825 --> 00:38:50.026
- It shouldn't be him.
- No. it needs to be.

728
00:38:58.853 --> 00:39:00.133
Hands on your head.

729
00:39:01.039 --> 00:39:03.940
Interlace your fingers.
Eyes front. Don't move.

730
00:39:16.621 --> 00:39:17.687
Other hand.

731
00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:23.760
Over here.

732
00:39:24.095 --> 00:39:25.489
You have the right
to remain silent.

733
00:39:25.513 --> 00:39:27.792
Anything you say
can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

734
00:39:27.816 --> 00:39:30.978
Come on!
We both know I won't live
to stand trial.

735
00:39:31.002 --> 00:39:32.202
Yes. you will.

736
00:39:33.137 --> 00:39:34.932
Because the woman
you killed taught us

737
00:39:34.956 --> 00:39:36.389
it's not our job to punish you.

738
00:39:37.075 --> 00:39:38.524
Just to see to it that you are.

739
00:39:58.112 --> 00:39:59.392
You coming?

740
00:40:10.342 --> 00:40:12.222
- What?
- No. don't...

741
00:40:16.097 --> 00:40:17.377
What the hell is wrong with you?

742
00:40:18.065 --> 00:40:19.877
Captain's dead.
and you're out here
spying on us?

743
00:40:19.901 --> 00:40:21.111
Your watch commander called.

744
00:40:21.135 --> 00:40:22.346
Said his people
were gonna do this right.

745
00:40:22.370 --> 00:40:24.610
wanted to make sure
that we saw it.

746
00:40:25.490 --> 00:40:27.856
Sorry about your captain.
I liked her.

747
00:40:29.928 --> 00:40:33.012
I also trashed
the conduct unbecoming charge.
so...

748
00:40:35.116 --> 00:40:37.436
You were right.
that was bush league.

749
00:40:37.919 --> 00:40:39.986
Good. Wait.

750
00:40:44.359 --> 00:40:46.420
Look. I'm only...
I'm only saying this.

751
00:40:46.444 --> 00:40:48.160
because Andersen
would want me to.

752
00:40:49.814 --> 00:40:50.897
But you were right. too.

753
00:40:52.050 --> 00:40:54.733
I knew Isabel
was using in the end. and...

754
00:40:55.553 --> 00:40:57.887
I didn't say anything because
I was trying to help her.

755
00:41:00.324 --> 00:41:01.324
She was my wife.

756
00:41:03.061 --> 00:41:04.221
How's she doing?

757
00:41:06.031 --> 00:41:08.097
Better. She's clean.

758
00:41:10.952 --> 00:41:12.072
I'm glad.

759
00:41:18.476 --> 00:41:20.759
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. for now.

760
00:41:22.230 --> 00:41:23.510
All right. back to work!

761
00:41:33.474 --> 00:41:34.490
What?

762
00:41:35.393 --> 00:41:37.553
First time I met the Captain.
I fell flat on my face.

763
00:41:38.930 --> 00:41:40.691
Bishop and Lopez sent me
to her office.

764
00:41:40.715 --> 00:41:42.443
told me
I needed to introduce myself

765
00:41:42.467 --> 00:41:43.978
- before roll call.
- You got punked.

766
00:41:44.002 --> 00:41:45.442
Yeah.
That's exactly what she said.

767
00:41:46.470 --> 00:41:49.684
Tried to play it off.
but she was
way too smart for that.

768
00:41:49.708 --> 00:41:50.708
Yeah.

769
00:41:54.028 --> 00:41:56.548
She asked for you to be assigned
to Mid-Wilshire. you know that?

770
00:41:58.416 --> 00:41:59.416
No.

771
00:42:00.969 --> 00:42:02.169
Why? She didn't even know me.

772
00:42:02.520 --> 00:42:04.165
She felt your experience
would make you

773
00:42:04.189 --> 00:42:05.949
a valuable addition
to our house.

774
00:42:09.160 --> 00:42:10.777
Guess I got a lot to live up to.

775
00:42:13.298 --> 00:42:14.298
We all do.

776
00:42:16.851 --> 00:42:18.131
We all do.
